## Repository Structure
safehome-ai/
│
├── scanner/ # Network discovery and risk analysis modules
├── reports/ # Report templates and generators
├── templates/ # Web interface templates
├── static/ # Static assets (CSS, images)
│
├── app.py # Main application entry point
├── engine.py # Core analysis and orchestration logic
├── requirements.txt # Python dependencies
├── sample_report.png # Sample output report


---

## Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.8 or higher  
- Local network access (for device discovery)  
- Administrator / sudo privileges (if required by the scanner)  

### Steps
```bash
git clone https://github.com/learnwithvidya/safehome-ai.git
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app:app --reload
Open on browser: http://127.0.0.1:8000/ui

----

